radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix demonstrates wall thickening and edema with a proximal measurement of up to 8 mm and a distal tip measurement of up to 13 mm; there is fat stranding in the vicinity. A 6 mm hypointense focus that could represent an appendicolith or gas is noted at the tip of the appendix. An intrauterine pregnancy is present with an anterior placenta, and the ovaries are unremarkable. No abnormalities in other abdominal organs; physiological free fluid in the pelvis; tiny fat containing umbilical hernia.
